---
source: crates/carta/tests/golden_e2e.rs
expression: output
---
Emphasis stays literal in "*quoted emphasis*" and strong in "**quoted
strong**".

Angle brackets also suppress markup as in \textless*not
emphasis*\textgreater.

Interpreted text in "`quoted interpreted text`" stays literal.

A phrase reference in "`quoted phrase`\_" and a simple reference in
"link\_" stay literal.

An inline literal "\texttt{stays\ code}" because literals are never
suppressed.
